HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1195
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Officer Codi Monroy
upon her receipt of the Lifesaving Medal.
WHEREAS, our nation was conceived by individuals who were willing to sacrifice their
personal concerns to ensure the public safety and welfare, and the Volunteer State is especially
proud to be the home of so many valiant individuals who have performed above and beyond the
call of duty in service of public safety; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Officer Codi Monroy of the Chattanooga Police
Department, who was recently awarded the Lifesaving Medal in recognition of her extraordinary
actions in the line of duty; and
WHEREAS, on October 24, 2025, Officer Monroy responded to Williams Street on a
report of an unconscious individual and, upon arrival, located a male experiencing a medical
emergency and immediately began rendering aid; and
WHEREAS, upon determining that the individual had no pulse, Officer Codi Monroy
initiated cardiopulmonary resuscitation and performed multiple cycles of CPR prior to the arrival
of fire and emergency medical personnel; and
WHEREAS, recognizing the signs of a possible opioid overdose, she administered
Narcan while continuing lifesaving measures, demonstrating sound judgment and decisive
action under critical circumstances; and
WHEREAS, as a direct result of Officer Monroy's efforts, the individual regained a pulse
and his condition stabilized, and her actions played a critical role in preserving his life; and
WHEREAS, Officer Codi Monroy has demonstrated the highest standards of
professionalism, courage, and dedication to duty, and her actions are worthy of special
recognition; now, therefore,
HJR1195
016038
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Officer Codi Monroy upon her receipt of the
Lifesaving Medal and extend to her our sincere appreciation for her heroic service to the people
of Tennessee.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
